Have you ever felt that sometimes you are your own worst enemy? We all have moments when, no matter how hard we try, things just don’t seem to work out right, when everything goes wrong, and we have no one to blame but ourselves. But, just as you may sometimes be your own worst enemy, you can also be your own best friend. The transition usually occurs when you realize that the only person on earth who can determine your failure or success is you yourself. You may discover your best friend when you develop the maturity and strength of character to accept yourself for the person you are and to take the actions necessary to become the person you wish to be. When you analyze yourself objectively, you can begin to build upon your strengths and compensate for your weaknesses. When you do, you will realize that the only person who stands in the way of your success is you.

The purpose of this question is to help you think through who you are and what you really want. These questions are to stimulate your creative thinking through focused question. Focusing is essential to the process of growing into your full potential. Without focusing and getting clarity, you cannot plan and you cannot discover your life dream. 
#teaser #focus #creative

CrossFit cambia vidas. 
Como coaches tenemos la responsabilidad de enseñar con el ejemplo. Tenemos que demostrar que podemos cambiar cualquier vida que entra por la puerta del box. La primera vida que tuvimos que cambiar fue la nuestra, a lo mejor no mucha gente sabia como éramos hace unos años. Hace 6 años hacia varias horas de ejercicio durante la semana y comía sano (evidentemente no lo suficiente). No existe pastilla magica. Solo dedicación y constancia. 
Agradecido que encontré este deporte y me cambio la vida. 
Coach Roberto Rueda
------------
CrossFit changes lives. 
As coaches we have an obligation to lead by example. We have to show we can change any life that walks in thru the door of the box. The first life we had to change was ours, maybe a lot of people didn't know where we were a couple of years ago. 6 years ago I was exercising a lot of hours in a week and eating well. (Clearly not well enough). There is no magic pill. It only takes hard work and consistency. 
Grateful I got into CrossFit and changed my lifestyle. 
Coach Roberto Rueda
